Fix memory leak and use-after-free when changing Style settings in Desktop Settings.

Two issues fixed:

 1. xfdesktop-file-icon-model-filter.c, finalize: monitor was
    g_value_dup_object'd in set_property but never g_object_unref'd.  Every
    time the icon style was switched away from "File launchers", one
    XfwMonitor ref leaked per filter instance.

 2. xfdesktop-icon-view-holder.c, finalize: the "notify::monitor" signal
    connected on holder->desktop (via plain g_signal_connect_swapped, which
    does not auto-disconnect) was never disconnected.  If the desktop's
    monitor property changed after the holder was freed, desktop_monitor_changed
    would access freed memory (use-after-free).

--- a/src/xfdesktop-file-icon-model-filter.c
+++ b/src/xfdesktop-file-icon-model-filter.c
@@ -362,4 +362,5 @@ xfdesktop_file_icon_model_filter_finalize(GObject *object) {
     XfdesktopFileIconModelFilter *filter = XFDESKTOP_FILE_ICON_MODEL_FILTER(object);
     g_object_unref(filter->channel);
+    g_object_unref(filter->monitor);
     G_OBJECT_CLASS(xfdesktop_file_icon_model_filter_parent_class)->finalize(object);
 }
--- a/src/xfdesktop-icon-view-holder.c
+++ b/src/xfdesktop-icon-view-holder.c
@@ -62,5 +62,6 @@ xfdesktop_icon_view_holder_finalize(GObject *object) {
     XfdesktopIconViewHolder *holder = XFDESKTOP_ICON_VIEW_HOLDER(object);

     g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_data(holder->monitor, holder);
+    g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_data(holder->desktop, holder);

     gtk_widget_destroy(holder->container);
